{"behaviors":[{"behavior_id":1,"description":"When a required key is absent from both the file and the environment, the error message names the missing key by its exact config path (e.g., `database.host`).","minimum_level":"Integration","justification":"Failure risk is at the handoff between config-file loading, env override merge, required-key validation, and CLI error rendering. A unit test of only the validator could miss path-shaping or source-merge bugs.","test_description":"Run the startup loader with a temp config file missing `database.host` and no matching `TOOL_...` env var set. Assert startup fails and emitted error text includes the exact dotted path `database.host`.","plan_consistent":true,"plan_consistent_note":null,"level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.32,"Integration":0.6,"System":0.06,"Agentic":0.01,"Workflow":0.01}},{"behavior_id":2,"description":"When the environment variable `XDG_CONFIG_HOME` is set, the loader resolves the config file path relative to that directory rather than `~/.config`.","minimum_level":"Integration","justification":"This behavior depends on interaction between environment lookup and path-resolution logic used by the loader. Mocking either side can hide wiring mistakes.","test_description":"Set `XDG_CONFIG_HOME` to a temp directory, place a valid config at `$XDG_CONFIG_HOME/tool/config.yaml`, and ensure startup reads that file (and not `~/.config/tool/config.yaml`) by asserting loaded values come from the temp location.","plan_consistent":true,"plan_consistent_note":null,"level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.28,"Integration":0.65,"System":0.06,"Agentic":0.005,"Workflow":0.005}},{"behavior_id":3,"description":"When an environment variable with the `TOOL_` prefix conflicts with a key in the config file, the environment variable value is used.","minimum_level":"Integration","justification":"Precedence bugs typically appear when file parsing, env normalization/mapping, and merge order are wired together. A unit test for merge alone may miss